$ Windows authentication

A → Windows/user-account[user] is authenticated by either
  • Interactive logon
  • Network logon (aka noninteractive authentication)

{ Integrated Windows Authentication

 *Integrated Windows Authentication* allows a → Windows/user-account to log in with his Windows credentials, either using
 → development/security/kerberos or → development/security/authentication/NTLM.

 Integrated Windows Authentication is also referred to by
   • HTTP Negotiate authentication
   • NT Authentication
   • Domain authentication
   • Windows NT Challenge/Response authentication
   • Windows authentication
   


}

sa:
  The → Windows/registry key
  → Windows/registry/tree/HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE/Software/Microsoft/Windows/CurrentVersion/Authentication[`HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\SOFTWARE\Microsoft\Windows\CurrentVersion\Authentication`]

  The `-useDefaultCredential` option of the → Windows/PowerShell/command-inventory/noun/webRequest/invoke[`invoke-webRequest`] cmdLet.

  The property → Microsoft/dot-net/namespaces-classes/System/Security/Principal/WindowsIdentity/AuthenticationType[`AuthenticationType`] of the
  → Microsoft/dot-net class → Microsoft/dot-net/namespaces-classes/System/Security/Principal/WindowsIdentity[`System.Security.Principal.WindowsIdentity`].

  → Windows/security/authentication/SSPI
